          title: "Regulation of the Minister of Trade Number 16 of 2025",
          date: "12 Dec 2025",
          content: "The Minister of Trade of the Republic of Indonesia has issued Regulation Number 16 of 2025 concerning the General Framework of Import Policies and Mechanisms. This milestone regulation serves as the master umbrella policy, integrating import channels via the OSS and INATRADE systems to support industrial stability.\n\n10 General Provisions & Definitions:\n1. Import Master Policy: The comprehensive umbrella regulation that establishes general guidelines and licensing structures for imports.\n2. Business Identification Number (NIB): The primary business number that also acts as the importer's identification number (API).\n3. INATRADE System: The electronic information system managed by the Ministry of Trade for import-export licensing.\n4. Online Single Submission (OSS): The integrated electronic licensing system for business activities in Indonesia.\n5. Taxpayer Status Verification (KSWP): The automated compliance check with tax databases prior to granting import approvals.\n6. Import Approval (PI): The official permit issued by the Ministry of Trade allowing the import of specific commodities.\n7. Surveyor Report (LS): The technical inspection document verified by an authorized surveyor at the port of origin.\n8. Commodity Clustering: The structural approach classifying imports into eight designated clusters with specific sub-regulations.\n9. Administrative Sanctions: Graduated penalties including warnings, suspension, or revocation of import privileges for violations.\n10. Domestic Industry Protection: Measures established to safeguard local manufacturers and balance trade flows.",
