          content: "The Director General of Taxes has issued Decree Number KEP-71/PJ/2026 concerning the Elimination of Administrative Sanctions for the Reporting of the 2025 Annual Income Tax Return (SPT). This policy is introduced in connection with the transition and implementation of the Core Tax Administration System (Coretax) to provide taxpayers additional time for adaptation without being penalized.\n\n10 General Provisions & Definitions:\n1. Elimination of Administrative Sanctions: The waiver of administrative fines and interest charges for late tax filing or payment.\n2. Taxpayer (WP): Individuals or corporate entities having tax obligations under the prevailing laws.\n3. Core Tax Administration System (Coretax): The new integrated tax administration system implemented by the Directorate General of Taxes (DJP).\n4. Annual Income Tax Return (SPT): The form used by taxpayers to report their annual income, tax payments, and assets.\n5. Directorate General of Taxes (DJP): The government agency responsible for tax collection and administration in Indonesia.\n6. Transition Period: The designated timeframe for adapting to the Coretax system during which relief policies apply.\n7. Due Date: The regular legal deadline for reporting the annual tax return.\n8. Tax Collection Letter (STP): The official letter issued to collect tax underpayments, administrative penalties, or fines.\n9. Ex-Officio Relief: The automatic elimination of administrative penalties by the tax office without requiring a taxpayer request.\n10. Compliance Status: The evaluation of a taxpayer's adherence to tax regulations, unaffected by late filings during this relief period.",
